This paper is primarily focused on intrusion detection in cyber security, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also proposes a methodology for countering adversarial attacks using machine learning algorithms, specifically random forests, which falls under the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing network traffic, which falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper discusses the integration of the proposed defense method in a cyber detector, which falls under the category of cs.SE (Software Engineering).
